2. Original ThemeForge palettes - Apache 2.0 (Julien Bombled)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Fourteen palettes engineered from declared geometric targets, not
reverse-engineered from hand-picked hexes :

  * All 10 Dark variants share a 7-accent band with uniform Oklab L*
    0.7185-0.7209. Hues are fixed at Cyan 186 deg, Green 135 deg,
    Orange 27 deg, Pink 333 deg, Purple 282 deg, Red 0 deg, Yellow 60 deg.
    Only the Background hue rotates between variants. The 7 accent hex values
    are byte-identical across the 10 Darks.

  * The 2 Light variants share a darker accent band with uniform Oklab L*
    0.4995-0.5012 so accents remain legible on bright surfaces.

  * The 2 Alt variants reuse the Dark band but break exactly one accent
    for their signature. The broken accent remains in the same Oklab L*
    band and raises chroma instead of brightness.

  * Comments on the Julien-authored variants target a uniform WCAG relative
    luminance around 0.38, clearing AA against Background and CurrentLine.

  * 15 of 16 palettes are AA-compliant on the contracted text pairs. The sole
    exception is Dracula's canonical MIT Comment color, preserved verbatim for
    historical fidelity. Drakul provides the AA-compliant sibling.

  Dark family (Background hue / character)
  - Striga          H  12 deg   Romanian night-witch, warm umber
  - Cinder          H  50 deg   mourning hearth, warm amber
  - Bracken         H 110 deg   dark fern, apothecary green
  - Tarn            H 170 deg   highland tarn, petrol-teal
  - Mortis          H 200 deg   slate-cyan morgue
  - Slate           H 225 deg   cold monastery stone, slate-blue
  - Voivode         H 255 deg   Wallachian throne, deep indigo
  - Carmilla        H 290 deg   velvet violet, Styrian countess (Le Fanu 1872)
  - Whitby          H 320 deg   North Sea slate-mauve, where Dracula came ashore
  - Vesper          H 345 deg   evening prayer in a ruined chapel

  Light family
  - Parchment       H  40 deg   warm vellum cream, scholarly hush
  - Folio           H 220 deg   cool ivory, stained-glass morning

  Alt family
  - Wormwood        Green broken to viridian (H 158 deg) - Green Fairy / absinthe
  - Sconce          Orange broken to amber (H 38 deg) - Victorian sconce

All names are drawn from public domain sources : folklore (Striga, Bracken, Tarn,
Mortis), architecture (Sconce, Folio, Parchment), atmosphere (Cinder, Vesper,
Slate), historical figures (Voivode = Romanian "warlord", Vlad III's title),
literature (Carmilla 1872, Whitby = Stoker 1897 setting), and herbal/biblical
references (Wormwood = Revelation 8:11 + Lewis's Screwtape Letters).

The "Dracula" name and Dracula PRO product are trademarks of Zeno Rocha. No
commercial Dracula PRO scheme name (Pro, Alucard, Blade, Buffy, Lincoln,
Morbius, Van Helsing) appears in this set.

================================================================================
Cross-review history
================================================================================

The v6 palette set is the result of five independent review passes performed on
2026-05-18 by independent reviewers :

  - Pass 1 / v2 : uniform-HSL-L initial set; HSL claims and AA failures found.
  - Pass 2 / v3 : exact HSL regeneration; Yellow and Comment failures found.
  - Pass 3 / v4 : uniform-WCAG-L pass; trademark and perception issues found.
  - Pass 4 / v5 : uniform-Oklab-L* accent bands; Sage and Dracula blockers found.
  - Pass 5 / v6 : Bracken rename plus Drakul sibling; final SHIP verdict.

